(11678, 'terbinafine', 'N/A', 'minor', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Terbinafine is an inhibitor of CYP4502D6 isozyme and has an effect on metabolism of desipramine, cimetidine, fluconazole, cyclosporine, rifampin, and caffeine. Terbinafine decreases the clearance of caffeine by 19%.', 'DailyMed'),
(11678, 'clozapine', 'N/A', 'moderate', '[see Dosage and Administration (2.6), Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)] Moderate or weak CYP1A2 inhibitors include oral contraceptives and caffeine.', 'DailyMed'),
