(1839, 'lexiscan(r) (regadenoson)', 'N/A', 'minor', '7.1 Effects of Other Drugs on LEXISCAN • Methylxanthines (e.g., caffeine, aminophylline and theophylline) are non-specific adenosine receptor antagonists that interfere with the vasodilation activity of LEXISCAN [see Clinical Pharmacology ( 12-12.2) and Patient Counseling Information ( 17)].', 'DailyMed'),
