(7737, 'lexiscan(r) (regadenoson)', 'N/A', 'minor', '7.1 Effects of Other Drugs on LEXISCAN • Methylxanthines (e.g., caffeine, aminophylline and theophylline) are non-specific adenosine receptor antagonists that interfere with the vasodilation activity of LEXISCAN [see Clinical Pharmacology ( 12-12.2) and Patient Counseling Information ( 17)].', 'DailyMed'),
(7737, 'stiripentol', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Because of potential drug-drug interactions, consider dose adjustment of CYP1A2 substrates (e.g., theophylline, caffeine), CYP2B6 substrates (e.g., sertraline, thiotepa), and CYP3A4 substrates (e.g., midazolam, triazolam, quinidine), as clinically appropriate, when administered concomitantly with DIACOMIT.', 'DailyMed'),
