(31972, 'regadenoson', 'N/A', 'minor', '•Methylxanthines, e.g., caffeine, aminophylline and theophylline, interfere with the activity of LEXISCAN (7.1, 12.2). 7.1 Effects of Other Drugs on LEXISCAN •Methylxanthines (e.g., caffeine, aminophylline and theophylline) are non-specific adenosine receptor antagonists that interfere with the vasodilation activity of LEXISCAN [see Clinical Pharmacology (12.2) and Patient Counseling Information (17)].', 'DailyMed'),
